\title{Inverse Operation}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{macros}
\def\inv{\text{inv}}
\p{
    Let #{A} be a type. The \strong{inverse oepration} is defined:
    ##{
        \inv: (x:A)\to (y:A)\to (x=_Ay)\to (y=_Ax)
    }
}
\block{
    \strong{Construction}
}{
    By induction, it suffices to construct:
    ##{
        \inv(x,x,\refl_x) : (x=_Ax)
    }
    for any #{x:A}. And trivially we have #{\inv(x,x,\refl_x)\equiv\refl_x}.
}
